notesStmt.note: This working group discussion among representatives from national and international youth organizations deals with problems and challenges concerning voluntary work. S1 is the chair of this subgroup, S7 is taking notes. S8 joins the group at a later point. The discussion takes place in a room where there are two other working groups, hence there is a high level of background noise. S2 and S5, who are the moderators of these working group discussions, join the subgroup from time to time to give instructions, sometimes they address all the subgroups present in the room.

equipment.p: Portable minidisc recorder with electret condenser stereo microphone

namespace.tagUsage: Used to mark a stretch of speech commonly preceded and followed by a pause or by a change of speaker. Auis, however, not required to be bounded by a pause or a change of speaker, nor does it represent a turn in a conversation analytic sense. At a minimum, auis some phonetic production or noise made by a given speaker or a group of speakers.
